{"id": "https://wineindustryadvisor.com/?p=148484", "url": "https://wineindustryadvisor.com/2026/05/22/why-packaging-decisions-cant-be-left-to-the-last-minute/", "title": "Why packaging decisions can’t be left to the last minute", "summary": "<img alt=\"\" class=\"webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"394\" src=\"https://wineindustryadvisor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/TXDXHBBNNVEA7FVBMVD4AV5Z6M-scaled.jpg\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" title=\"foodnavigator-usa.com\" width=\"640\" /><p><img alt=\"\" class=\"attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image\" height=\"984\" src=\"https://wineindustryadvisor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/TXDXHBBNNVEA7FVBMVD4AV5Z6M-scaled.jpg\" title=\"foodnavigator-usa.com\" width=\"1600\" /></p>Packaging can no longer be treated as a final step in product development, rather these decisions need to be made much earlier and far more holistically, according to Greg Lawson, managing director of packaging consultancy firm Aura Global. For food and beverage brands, the biggest packaging decisions are often made too late when costs are locked in, flexibility is gone and compliance risks are harder to manage, according to one industry expert.", "content": "<img alt=\"\" class=\"webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"394\" src=\"https://wineindustryadvisor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/TXDXHBBNNVEA7FVBMVD4AV5Z6M-scaled.jpg\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" title=\"foodnavigator-usa.com\" width=\"640\" /><p><img alt=\"\" class=\"attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image\" height=\"984\" src=\"https://wineindustryadvisor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/TXDXHBBNNVEA7FVBMVD4AV5Z6M-scaled.jpg\" title=\"foodnavigator-usa.com\" width=\"1600\" /></p>Packaging can no longer be treated as a final step in product development, rather these decisions need to be made much earlier and far more holistically, according to Greg Lawson, managing direct